terminology.controls:
*It is recommended to turn `allow backwards wallriding` on and `walljump on release` off. Lucio's air movement is affected by your viewing direction, looking up gains height while looking down loses it.*

[more info](https://discord.com/channels/574522788967088128/579836384085278720/963132673314934844)
terminology.jump:
*Jumps are the easiest and most intuitive thing about Lucio's advanced movement kit, just go to a wall and press your jump button twice.*

[more info](https://discord.com/channels/574522788967088128/579836384085278720/963038438158917642)
terminology.skim:
*Skims are the fastest way of travel for Lucio. To perform a skim go to a wall and do two consecutive one frame long jump inputs.*

[more info](https://discord.com/channels/574522788967088128/579836384085278720/729395454738956308)
terminology.onetick:
*Oneticks help bridge gaps that are too short for another skim but too long for a longskim. To perform them just go to a wall and do one one frame long jump input.*

[more info](https://discord.com/channels/574522788967088128/579836384085278720/729414075984904212)
terminology.latejump:
*Latejumps are the same as jumps but the second jump input is delayed by around 0.2 secs. They give your jump more length.*

[more info](https://discord.com/channels/574522788967088128/579836384085278720/729402282621272116)
terminology.lateskim:
*Lateskims are the same as skims but the second jump input is delayed by around 0.2 secs. They give your jump more length while retaining the speed advantages of a skim over a jump.*

[more info](https://discord.com/channels/574522788967088128/579836384085278720/729404743377485835)
terminology.headhit:
*Headhits are skims or jumps on which you hit your head on a ceiling to transform your upwards momentum into downwards momentum without losing speed.*

[more info](https://discord.com/channels/574522788967088128/579836384085278720/729657922967044168)
terminology.ceilingBoost:
*Ceiling boosts work like headhits but on a slanted ceiling to transform your upwards into forwards momentum.*

[more info](https://discord.com/channels/574522788967088128/579836384085278720/729660571359903814)
terminology.curveBoost:
*Curve boosts are achieved by doing a jump on a curved wall to achieve some extra speed.*

[more info](https://discord.com/channels/574522788967088128/579836384085278720/729416962391801896)
terminology.rampSlide:
*Ramp slides are used for building speed. They work by dropping onto a slanted, non-wallridable surface.*

[more info](https://discord.com/channels/574522788967088128/579836384085278720/963138743722721360)
terminology.vCurve:
*V-Curves are used to clear small overhangs. They are done by long jumping but turning 180¬∞ and looking up before your second jump input.*

[more info](https://discord.com/channels/574522788967088128/579836384085278720/729421900253757553)
